═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
USING SPRITES IN BRUSHES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Reference your sprites in Brush XML files using the Sprite attribute:

<Brush Name="MyTheme.Button">
  <Layers>
    <BrushLayer Name="Default" Sprite="my_button_9" Color="#FFD700FF" />
  </Layers>
  <Styles>
    <Style Name="Hovered">
      <BrushLayer Name="Default" Color="#FFFFFFFF" />
    </Style>
  </Styles>
</Brush>

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
TIPS FOR THEME AUTHORS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. COLOR TINTING: Use white/grayscale sprites with Color attribute for easy theming
   <BrushLayer Name="Default" Sprite="BlankWhiteSquare_9" Color="#FFD700FF" />

2. SPRITE NAMING: Use backslash for paths: "MyTheme\sprite_name"

3. SHEET ORGANIZATION: Group related sprites together in your sprite sheet

4. 9-SLICE BORDERS: Keep corner sizes consistent for uniform appearance

5. TRANSPARENCY: Use PNG with alpha channel for overlays and glows

6. SIZE OPTIMIZATION: Use smallest power-of-2 that fits your sprites

7. EXISTING SPRITES: You can override existing sprites by using the same name

8. HUE/SATURATION: BrushLayers support HueFactor, SaturationFactor, ValueFactor
   for color manipulation without replacing sprites

